Introduction to the medicine is the basic subject for the students who just started their medical studies. The peculiarity of medical education in the world and in Estonia, academical staff, structure, research activities and workflow of the faculty are discussed. The students are introduced with Estonian healthcare system and residency training principles.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide basic knowledge about peculiarity of medical education, Faculty of Medicine  and also about the basic principles of Estonian health system.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who graduated the course: a) has analysed the skills and competences of medical doctor and is aware of his own learning needs   b) analysed himself as a learner, has planned his studies and knows how to choose suitable learning strategies c) has experienced teamwork and has analysed the necessary conditions for teamwork d) has discussed on ethical aspects in medical studies e) has reflected on his own studies and professional development as future doctor
